As shown in Table 1, the trust propagation distance from the active user to the recommenders should be no longer than the maximum allowable trust propagation distance. If the trust propagation distance is too long, the recommendations given by the recommender may have very limited effects on the rating prediction, while this greatly increases the recommender searching cost. It has been verified in the related works that when setting a suitable value for the maximum allowable trust propagation distance, TARS can achieve high rating prediction accuracy with almost similar rating prediction coverage as searching the whole trust network.

